main event: Nine spherical objects were seen on ground radar traveling at approximately 6,000 mph for about 9.5 minutes on 28/05/1957.
interesting points: Objects were traveling at an incredibly high speed of 6,000 mph.
The observation lasted for exactly nine and a half minutes.
The objects were initially thought to be caused by atmospheric conditions.
The sighting was associated with possible meteor activity.
The report was sent for analysis but was deemed to add little or nothing to the current knowledge of UFOs.
witnesses: personnel at the 2035th AACS and 93D AREFS
